    <div class="textbox_about">
        <h2>Ebay Office Chairs Within 20 km Of Copenhagen</h2>
        <div class="text_flex">
        <p>Per Lunde Jørgensen's popular works are based on office chairs found and purchased on the Danish sales platform Den Blå Avis within a limited search radius of 20 km. The covering of the office chair is removed and sewn onto a textile canvas for pictorial objects. They exist in an unstable state between the recognizable and the generally abstract.</p>

        <p>In a previous exhibition at the Bonamatic gallery in 2018, these works were the focus. The exhibition's title, 'Reassembling the Social,' is taken from Bruno Latour's book of the same name. It points to how the works, in various ways, contemplate our arrangement of the social by actively intervening in it with new objects. They raise questions about the distribution of roles between the subjective and the objective and how what appears as static is sometimes mutable.</p>
        </div>
